speaker: First Murderer
text: It was, so please your Highness.

speaker: First Murderer
text: You made it known to us.

speaker: First Murderer
text: We are men, my liege.

speaker: First Murderer
text: And I another

speaker: First Murderer
text: So weary with disasters, tugged with fortune,

speaker: First Murderer
text: That I would set my life on any chance,

speaker: First Murderer
text: To mend it or be rid on ’t.

speaker: First Murderer
text: True, my lord.

speaker: First Murderer
text: Though our lives—

speaker: First Murderer
text: We are resolved, my lord.

speaker: First Murderer
text: But who did bid thee join with us?

speaker: First Murderer
text: Then stand with us.—

speaker: First Murderer
text: The west yet glimmers with some streaks of day.

speaker: First Murderer
text: Now spurs the lated traveler apace

speaker: First Murderer
text: To gain the timely inn, and near approaches

speaker: First Murderer
text: The subject of our watch.

speaker: First Murderer
text: His horses go about.

speaker: First Murderer
text: Stand to ’t.

speaker: First Murderer
text: Let it come down!

speaker: First Murderer
text: Was ’t not the way?

speaker: First Murderer
text: Well, let’s away and say how much is done.

speaker: First Murderer
text: ’Tis Banquo’s then.

speaker: First Murderer
text: My lord, his throat is cut. That I did for him.

speaker: First Murderer
text: Most royal sir, Fleance is ’scaped.

speaker: First Murderer
text: Ay, my good lord. Safe in a ditch he bides,

speaker: First Murderer
text: With twenty trenchèd gashes on his head,

speaker: First Murderer
text: The least a death to nature.
